==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amulet
<hw>Am"u*let</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>amuletum</ets>: cf. F. <ets>amulette</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
ornament, gem, or scroll, or a package containing a relic, etc., worn as
a charm or preservative against evils or mischief, such as diseases and
witchcraft, and generally inscribed with mystic forms or characters.
<note>[Also used figuratively.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amuletic</ent>⟦br⟧
